<collectingCountry box="[334,407,1842,1867]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Brazil</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
: AM, MT!, MG, SP.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1842,2014]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,409,1881,1906]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Biological aspects</emphasis>
: Representatives of this species have been collected on a 
<number box="[1057,1071,1882,1906]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" value="1.0">1</number>
st order environment upstream of a waterfall on a preserved stream with direct incidence of light. The marginal vegetation is composed by native grass and few bushes, typical of the 
<emphasis box="[556,651,1954,1978]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Cerrado</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="219" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1842,2014]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="219" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1989,2014]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Comments</emphasis>
: This species is distributed from 
<collectingCountry box="[700,784,1989,2014]" name="Canada" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Canada</collectingCountry>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[819,933,1989,2014]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrometridae" genus="Hydrometra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentina">
<collectingCountry box="[819,933,1989,2014]" name="Argentina" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Argentina</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
, but very few collections have been made on tropical areas. In 
<collectingCountry box="[346,417,151,176]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it was previously known from the North and Southeast, being herein recorded for the first time from the Central-West (
<figureCitation box="[473,556,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1694,1717]" captionTargetBox="[300,1286,306,1669]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[298,1288,303,1669]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Predicted distribution of Microvelia hinei in Brazil based on literature and collections on eastern Mato Grosso." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222387/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
